name: COVID19ICD10CMValueSetForPrematureInfant37WeeksGestation
title: COVID19 ICD10CM Value Set for Premature Infant (< 37 Weeks Gestation)
purpose: (Clinical Focus: This set of values contains terms related to premature infant < 37 weeks gestation at birth and is listed as an underlying medical condition, for pediatric cases only, on the CDC SARS-CoV-2 hospitalization surveillance case report form.),(Data Element Scope: ),(Inclusion Criteria: Includes premature infant < 37 weeks gestation at birth.),(Exclusion Criteria: Excludes > or = 37 weeks gestational age at birth.)
